 Wednesday, May 26, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, May 25: The new Congress-led government under economist-turned-politician Manmohan Singh got a shot in the arm with exports surging by almost 20 per cent in April. The countrys exports started on a positive note with a 19.95 per cent rise at $5.01 billion in April, from $4.18 billion a year ago. The significant factor is that exports in all sectors have shown an increase in April, which augurs well for the economy, trade analysts said. The countrys imports rose by 20.78 per cent at $6.75 billion as against $5.59 billion in April 2003.																								 New Delhi, May 25: The infrastructure sectors growth doubled to 9 per cent in April against 4.5 per cent in the year-ago period. The growth in six core sectors during the first month of this fiscal was also higher than the 7.2 per cent growth rate recorded in March 2004. 																								 Mumbai, May 25: Idea Cellular Ltd has recast its top deck and appointed a number of senior management personnel, including Sudhir Mathur as chief financial officer and S. Ramaswamy as vice-president, service delivery and quality.																								 Mumbai, May 25: The Reserve Bank of India has suggested that all public and private sector banks should increase their direct lending to agriculture to 12 per cent of net bank credit within two years.																								 New Delhi, May 25: Telecom regulator Trai today extended the date for filing of accounting separation manual by service providers to July 15 from May 23 stipulated earlier, following representations from the industry.
